title: First British victim of Egypt dive boat fire named as tributes paid
description: One of the three British passengers who died on a diving boat that caught fire in Egypt has been named.

title: Highway to 'Hel' journey banned after religious groups object to 'Satanic' 666 bus route
description: Tourists taking the highway to Hel will no longer be able travel on bus route 666 after religious groups said the reference to "the number of the beast" - viewed by some as a harmless joke - was "Satanic stupidity".

title: Thousands gather for state funeral of former Italian prime minister Silvio Berlusconi
description: Thousands of mourners have gathered to bid a final farewell to former Italian prime minister Silvio Berlusconi.

title: At least 78 dead after fishing boat sinks
description: At least 78 people have died and dozens are feared missing after a fishing boat carrying migrants sank off the coast of southern Greece, authorities have said.

title: Rescue dog used to help find plane crash children in Colombian jungle is missing
description: As four children who survived a plane crash in the Colombian jungle recover in hospital, the search is continuing - for the dog who helped save them.

title: Man faked own death and turned up at funeral in helicopter
description: A Belgian TikToker faked his own death to find out who cared and then turned up to his own funeral.

title: World's most famous human ancestor 'could walk just like us'
description: The world's most famous early human ancestor could walk upright like a modern-day human thanks to fully bendable knee joints, research suggests.

title: Belarus 'starts receiving tactical nuclear weapons from Russia three times more powerful than Hiroshima bomb'
description: Belarus has started to receive tactical nuclear weapons from Russia, its leader has said.

title: Weapons expert 'likely hungover' on set when Alec Baldwin shot dead cinematographer
description: The weapons supervisor on the film set where Alec Baldwin shot and killed a cinematographer has been accused of smoking and drinking in the evenings during filming.
